      "content": "thanks that's helpful. so if the originalist way is the more rigorous one, then doesn't that mean the recent court rulings are more 'legitimate' in a legal sense? i mean if they are following a more structured, evidence-based framework, isn't the other side just basically just politics disguised as law?",
